<!-- Process — bordered grid cells, not cards -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section-head section-head-left">
      <p class="eyebrow">How it ships</p>
      <h2>Four weeks,<br>start to live.</h2>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-grid">
      <li class="process-step reveal">
        <span class="step-num">01 — Map</span>
        <h3>Strategy first</h3>
        <p>We audit the product, audience, and the metric. You get a one-page strategy brief, not a slide deck.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step reveal">
        <span class="step-num">02 — Sketch</span>
        <h3>Two directions, fast</h3>
        <p>We commit early and iterate in the open. Nothing is precious; everything is reviewable on day three.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step reveal">
        <span class="step-num">03 — Build</span>
        <h3>Production design</h3>
        <p>Production-ready files, front-end if needed, reviewed daily, approved weekly, shipped on Friday.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="process-step reveal">
        <span class="step-num">04 — Compound</span>
        <h3>Launch is week one</h3>
        <p>Everything after launch is iteration with data, not opinion. We stay on until the metric moves.</p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

